three hours after marriage was a restoration comedy , written in 1717 as a collaboration between john gay , alexander pope and john arbuthnot , though gay was the principal author . it premiered in 1717 .   the play is best described as a satirical farce , and among its satirical targets was richard blackmore .   three hours after marriage tells the story of dr fossil , a pompous ageing scientist , who has just married a much younger woman , who is then immediately beset by two rival suitors who try to win her affections .   the wife and suitors then go to comical lengths to hide their intentions from dr fossil .